  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the configuration settings of a pro Counter Strike 1.6 player?",
  "response": "The configuration settings of a pro Counter-Strike 1.6 player are highly tailored to their personal preferences and play style, but there are several common elements that many professional players tend to use. Below are some key aspects that pros typically configure:\n\n### Video Settings:\n1. **Resolution**: Often set to lower values like 640x480 or 800x600 for better visibility and performance.\n2. **Color Quality**: High or True Color (32-bit).\n3. **Brightness/Gamma**: Adjusted to make enemies more visible.\n4. **Vertical Sync**: Usually disabled to ensure better frame rates and reduce input lag.\n\n### Mouse Settings:\n1. **Sensitivity**: This varies widely but generally is kept low for more precise aiming, usually between 1.5 to 3.0.\n2. **Acceleration**: Typically disabled (m_rawinput 1; m_filter 0).\n3. **Polling Rate**: Set to the maximum rate supported by their mouse (usually 1000 Hz).\n4. **DPI**: Commonly set to a low value such as 400 or 800.\n\n### Crosshair Settings:\n1. **Crosshair Color**: Bright colors like green or red for visibility.\n2. **Size**: Often small but designed to be clearly visible.\n3. **Dynamic Crosshair**: Usually set to static to ensure consistency.\n\n### Keyboard and Bindings:\n1. **Key Bindings**: Customized to optimize quick access, for example:\n   - `bind mwheelup \"+jump\"` to bunny hop.\n   - `bind mwheeldown \"slot1\"` for quick weapon switch.\n   - `bind mouse3 \"use weapon_flashbang\"` for quick grenade use.\n2. **Duck and Walk**: Easily accessible keys, often bound to Shift and Ctrl.\n3. **Communication**: Voice and tactical call keys bound to quick access.\n\n### Network Settings:\n1. **Rates**:\n   - `rate 25000`\n   - `cl_cmdrate 101`\n   - `cl_updaterate 101`\n2. **Ex_interp**: Typically set to `0.01` or `0.1` depending on preference.\n\n### Audio Settings:\n1. **Volume**: High enough to hear footsteps and other game cues clearly.\n2. **Speaker Configuration**: Set to \"Headphones\" or \"Stereo\" for accurate directional sound.\n\n### Advanced Configuration (Advanced Users):\n1. **Config Files**: Custom configs which contain all settings to ensure consistency (config.cfg, autoexec.cfg).\n2. **Launch Options**:\n   - `-noforcemaccel -noforcemspd -noforcemparms` for mouse consistency across the game and desktop.\n   - `-freq 100` or `-freq 144` to set the monitor refresh rate to 100Hz or 144Hz.\n\n### Practice and Warm-up:\n1. **Custom Maps**: Using maps specifically designed for aim training like \"aim_map\" or \"training_aim_cz\".\n\n### General Preferences:\nThese personal settings are usually refined over years of playing. Players often experiment with different settings until they find the perfect balance that works for them.\n\nIt\u2019s important to remember that the optimal settings can be highly subjective. What works for one player may not necessarily work for another, so aspiring pros should test various configurations to see what feels best for them.",
